verses.text_plain: Moreover Job continued his parable, and said,
verses.verse_html:
1Moreover Job continued his parable, and said, ▼
▼ continued: Heb. added to take up

footnotes.body_text: ▼ continued: Heb. added to take up
footnotes.body_html: ▼ continued: Heb. added to take up

verses.text_plain: Oh that I were as in months past, as in the days when God preserved me;
verses.verse_html: 2Oh that I were as in months past, as in the days when God preserved me;

verses.text_plain: When his candle shined upon my head, and when by his light I walked through darkness;
verses.verse_html:
3When his candle shined upon my head, and when by his light I walked through darkness; ▼
▼ candle: or, lamp

verses.text_plain: As I was in the days of my youth, when the secret of God was upon my tabernacle;
verses.verse_html: 4As I was in the days of my youth, when the secret of God was upon my tabernacle;

tokens.text: As I was in the days

verses.text_plain: When the Almighty was yet with me, when my children were about me;
verses.verse_html: 5When the Almighty was yet with me, when my children were about me;

verses.text_plain: When I washed my steps with butter, and the rock poured me out rivers of oil;
verses.verse_html:
6When I washed my steps with butter, and the rock poured me out rivers of oil; ▼
▼ me: Heb. with me

footnotes.body_html: ▼ me: Heb. with me

verses.text_plain: When I went out to the gate through the city, when I prepared my seat in the street!
verses.verse_html: 7When I went out to the gate through the city, when I prepared my seat in the street!

verses.text_plain: The young men saw me, and hid themselves: and the aged arose, and stood up.
verses.verse_html: 8The young men saw me, and hid themselves: and the aged arose, and stood up.

verses.text_plain: The princes refrained talking, and laid their hand on their mouth.
verses.verse_html: 9The princes refrained talking, and laid their hand on their mouth.

verses.text_plain: The nobles held their peace, and their tongue cleaved to the roof of their mouth.
verses.verse_html:
10The nobles held their peace, and their tongue cleaved to the roof of their mouth. ▼
▼ The nobles…: Heb. The voice of the nobles was hid

tokens.text: to the roof of their mouth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ The nobles…: Heb. The voice of the nobles was hid
footnotes.body_html: ▼ The nobles…: Heb. The voice of the nobles was hid

verses.text_plain: When the ear heard me, then it blessed me; and when the eye saw me, it gave witness to me:
verses.verse_html: 11When the ear heard me, then it blessed me; and when the eye saw me, it gave witness to me:

verses.text_plain: Because I delivered the poor that cried, and the fatherless, and him that had none to help him.
verses.verse_html: 12Because I delivered the poor that cried, and the fatherless, and him that had none to help him.

verses.text_plain: The blessing of him that was ready to perish came upon me: and I caused the widow’s heart to sing for joy.
verses.verse_html: 13The blessing of him that was ready to perish came upon me: and I caused the widow’s heart to sing for joy.

tokens.text: of him that was ready to perish
upon me: and I caused the widow’s

verses.text_plain: I put on righteousness, and it clothed me: my judgment was as a robe and a diadem.
verses.verse_html: 14I put on righteousness, and it clothed me: my judgment was as a robe and a diadem.

verses.text_plain: I was eyes to the blind, and feet was I to the lame.
verses.verse_html: 15I was eyes to the blind, and feet was I to the lame.

verses.text_plain: I was a father to the poor: and the cause which I knew not I searched out.
verses.verse_html: 16I was a father to the poor: and the cause which I knew not I searched out.

verses.text_plain: And I brake the jaws of the wicked, and plucked the spoil out of his teeth.
verses.verse_html:
17And I brake the jaws of the wicked, and plucked the spoil out of his teeth. ▼
▼ the jaws: Heb. the jawteeth, or, the grinders
 , ▼
▼ plucked: Heb. cast

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the jaws: Heb. the jawteeth, or, the grinders
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the jaws: Heb. the jawteeth, or, the grinders

verses.text_plain: Then I said, I shall die in my nest, and I shall multiply my days as the sand.
verses.verse_html: 18Then I said, I shall die in my nest, and I shall multiply my days as the sand.

verses.text_plain: My root was spread out by the waters, and the dew lay all night upon my branch.
verses.verse_html:
19My root was spread out by the waters, and the dew lay all night upon my branch. ▼
▼ spread…: Heb. opened

verses.text_plain: My glory was fresh in me, and my bow was renewed in my hand.
verses.verse_html:
20My glory was fresh in me, and my bow was renewed in my hand. ▼
▼ fresh: Heb. new
 , ▼
▼ renewed: Heb. changed

verses.text_plain: Unto me men gave ear, and waited, and kept silence at my counsel.
verses.verse_html: 21Unto me men gave ear, and waited, and kept silence at my counsel.

verses.text_plain: After my words they spake not again; and my speech dropped upon them.
verses.verse_html: 22After my words they spake not again; and my speech dropped upon them.

verses.text_plain: And they waited for me as for the rain; and they opened their mouth wide as for the latter rain.
verses.verse_html: 23And they waited for me as for the rain; and they opened their mouth wide as for the latter rain.

tokens.text: for me as for the rain

verses.text_plain: If I laughed on them, they believed it not; and the light of my countenance they cast not down.
verses.verse_html: 24If I laughed on them, they believed it not; and the light of my countenance they cast not down.

verses.text_plain: I chose out their way, and sat chief, and dwelt as a king in the army, as one that comforteth the mourners.
verses.verse_html: 25I chose out their way, and sat chief, and dwelt as a king in the army, as one that comforteth the mourners.
